
Java 17 Features (Interview Important + Examples) ⭐

Java 17 is a Long-Term Support (LTS) version and is widely used in Spring Boot enterprise applications.


1. Sealed Classes ⭐
...........................
Sealed classes restrict which classes can extend or implement them.


Why Do We Need Sealed Classes?

Suppose you're developing a Banking System.

You have an Account class, and you want only these account types:

SavingsAccount
CurrentAccount
LoanAccount

No other developer should be able to create:

GoldAccount
PremiumAccount
UnknownAccount

A sealed class enforces this restriction.


Example
public sealed class Payment
        permits UpiPayment, CardPayment {
}
Allowed subclasses
public final class UpiPayment
        extends Payment {
}
public final class CardPayment
        extends Payment {
}
Invalid ❌
public class CashPayment
        extends Payment {
}

Not allowed → compilation error.

Benefits

✔ Controlled inheritance
✔ Better security
✔ Useful with pattern matching

2. Pattern Matching for switch (Preview in Java 17) ⭐
...........................................
Improves switch logic with type checks.

Example
static String process(Object obj) {

    return switch (obj) {

        case Integer i ->
                "Integer: " + i;

        case String s ->
                "String: " + s;

        case Double d ->
                "Double: " + d;

        default ->
                "Unknown Type";
    };
}
Usage
System.out.println(process("Java"));
System.out.println(process(100));
Output
String: Java
Integer: 100
Benefits

✔ No instanceof checks
✔ Cleaner code
✔ More readable switch

3. Strong Encapsulation of JDK Internals ⭐
.............................................
Java 17 strongly hides internal APIs.

Before
Unsafe internal APIs were accessible
After Java 17
Internal APIs are strongly encapsulated
Benefits

✔ Better security
✔ Stable Java platform

